-- MOVES-Danske Bank names acting head of group risk management
-- 
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 05:59AM EDT
-- None



COPENHAGEN, Sept 19 (Reuters) - Denmark's largest listed bank Danske Bank <DANSKE.CO> has appointed Peter Rostrup-Nielsen as acting head of group risk management from Dec. 1.

He will take over from Robert Endersby, who has been a member of the bank's executive board since 2012. Endersby is to step down from his position on Nov. 30.